2500|$|The speculators {{attempted}} to bet against the Real, forcing a devaluation by the Central Bank. While Franco {{was in the}} Bank, however, the currency followed a <b>linear</b> <b>devaluation</b> of about 6% per year, even during periods of international turbulence, such as the Asian financial crisis in 1997 and the Russian financial crisis in 1998. In a few occasions, Franco himself {{took control of the}} currency bidding operations. [...] Using his knowledge and the legal authority of the Central Bank, Franco imposed heavy losses on the speculators.|$|E

